title: A Year With the Saints
creator: Anonymous
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text
description: LibriVox recording of A YEAR WITH THE SAINTS, by Anonymous. Read by Maria Therese. Go through the year in the footsteps of the saints. This book emphasizes one virtue for each month with quotes and stories from the lives of the saints to help teach and inspire that particular virtue in us. For January, Perfection; February, Humility; March, Mortification; April, Patience; May, Meekness; June, Obedience; July, Simplicity; August, Diligence; September, Prayer; October, Confidence; November, Charity; and December, Union. (Summary by Maria Therese) For further information, including links to M4B audio book, online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.
subject: librivox; audiobook; Catholic; saints; virtues; morals; sanctity

reviews.reviewbody: This wonderfully performed version of "A Year With the Saints" is a fascinating overview of adherence.  It stands out with its brilliant topical organization and vivid illustrations from respected practitioners.
